{{Infobox number | number = 269 | prime = yes }} '''269''' ('''two hundred [and] sixty-nine''') is the natural number between [[268 (number)#Other numbers from 261 to 269|268]] and [[270 (number)|270]]. It is also a [[prime number]].
==In mathematics== 269 is a [[twin prime]],<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A001359|name=Lesser of twin primes}}</ref> and a [[Ramanujan prime]].<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A104272|name=Ramanujan primes}}</ref> It is the largest prime factor of 9!&nbsp;+&nbsp;1&nbsp;=&nbsp;362881,<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A002583|name=Largest prime factor of n! + 1}}</ref> and the smallest natural number that cannot be represented as the [[determinant]] of a 10&nbsp;&times;&nbsp;10 [[Logical matrix|(0,1)-matrix]].<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A013588|name=Smallest positive integer not the determinant of an n X n 0-1 matrix}}</ref> ==See also== * [[Area code 269]] * [[Calf 269]] animal liberation movement * [[Hawkmoon 269]] pop song by [[U2]] * [[List of highways numbered 269]]
