In [[combinatorics|combinatorial mathematics]], a '''picture''' is a [[bijection]] between [[Young tableau#Skew tableaux|skew diagrams]] satisfying certain properties, introduced by {{harvtxt|Zelevinsky|1981}} in a generalization of the [[Robinson–Schensted correspondence]] and the [[Littlewood–Richardson rule]].

